This paper deals with domain adaptation in imitation learning, which is a problem commonly studied in the machine learning community. The paper presents statistical learning guarantees for third-person imitation from observation, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves learning from observation. The paper also deals with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves learning policies for decision making. Finally, the paper presents a lower bound on performance, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY).
